This was my first time going to Mezeh in that location and I walked in but none of the employee's came to the counter to help me but this nice young lady. She was very patient and even suggested what I should get since I wanted to switch up my order. She even helped me out at the register. I'm glad she was working when I walked in!

Had Mezeh for the first time ever today. Had a chicken and lamb bowl with extra sauce and an extra pita. It was top 5. I’m only here because after i ate that bowl. I felt compelled to tell somebody. Thank you for coming to my TED Talk.
I get a wrap. Lamb meatballs, greens, brown rice, red cabbage, and Tzatziki salad dressing.
This is  one of my favorite local spots. They have the most amazing sandwiches and  fries!!!!!! If you haven't tried this place do it now. You won't be disappointed!
First time here. Food was good. Server appeared to have a stank attitude which is why the low rating.

To quote my 9 y/o, “YUCK”. We eat at Cava regularly and love Mediterranean food so decided we’d give Mezeh a try.  If there were a Zero star option, that is what they would score.  From the beginning of our experience, my 9 y/o was irritated by how slow and inattentive the young lady serving her was behaving. We persisted. We both ordered and even got a juice from the “juice bar” to have the entire Mezeh experience. Quoting the child again, “mommy, we should have just put the $25.12 in the trash.” Mezeh, visit Cava, see how it’s done from start to finish.
Always fresh and always delicious! Love that I get to pick what you want and how much. Often crowded but it's freshly made and things move pretty fast.  I go again and again.

Food here was great! I do wish there was suggested pairings like at CAVA. I appreciate the health flair and the healthier soda options. My husband and I had similar bowls but weren't really sure how to make a tasty combo. Spinach, white basmati rice, shredded lamb, hummus, cucumbers, pickled onions, beets, feta, and dressing. We have no idea what dressing we got but out was delicious. Both bowls we're served with half a pita. The location reminds me of Chipotle but with a mediterranean flair.
Absolutely delicious food and great customer service!
The food is delicious and the staff is very friendly.

I do love all the different flavors Mezeh has to offer! They are a little skimpy on the portions,  but I need to lose a little anyway...but overall I do love the food!!!  Side note...they will make online orders before they take your order, stood there for a good 7 minutes before they even looked at us.

Its like Chipotle meets Mediterranean heaven.  I love this place, the food is amazing.  So many choices, so many nutritious options.  Great place to grab a healthy and well balanced meal.  Try the juice bar too!
Quick, fresh,  and tasty.
So so sooo good!! Lots of unique toppings and fast service. Pretty great prices for amount of food, too!
If you are vegetarian/vegan you absolutely need to try it. This is exactly how we need to be eating. Colorful, fresh veggies. Great prices, amazing taste. It doesn’t get any better!
Super slow but my food was delicious

it was good! I personally like it better than Cava. It's more flavorful/better seasoned. I had a bowl with rice, chicken shawarma and falafel. they have a ton of authentic topics including pickled radish and onions!

I don't know about you, but I eat with my eyes first! The establishment was very clean. My eyes feasted upon glass jars of spices and non-perishable items of ethnic goodness. The number of options (at least 12) for a bowl were more than Chipotle, Spice 6, Subway, &Pizza, FiveGuys, or any other chain restaurants which offer fresh vegetables as toppings. I guess the business that offers most options wins.....

I would love to rate the food but since half my order was missing I have no idea what it would have tasted like.  What's more, no one answered the phone when I attempted to call to alert the store.  Bad business Mezha.

The bowl I created was good, I liked the lamb.  They have lots of options to top it with. However,  the caramel salted cookie?  Oh man that was the best cookie I have ever had.  Sweet, salty, I think cream cheese or white chocolate inside.

The food is always delicious, tasty and fresh. I ordered the rice bowl with, spinach, chicken and my favorite toppings. It reminds me of chipotle where you can add as many topping as you like so I enjoy experimenting. I recommend visiting if you have a taste for Mediterranean food.  You will not be disappointed!
Becoming addicted to this place...easy parking. Clean restaurant.
very good food

Great food and reasonably priced. Thanks to Mayra for providing outstanding customer service and helping me select a sauce for my bowl. I plan to return in the near future.

This is a solid place. The food is good, the service is great, and the manager is definitely the leader of the pack. This place takes care of their customers. I look forward to going there again and thanking the manager for such a great service.

Love. Love. Love. I'm working in Bowie for a few months, and I will say that it is truly dangerous that they are maybe 5min from my office. Plotting and planning lol- I always order thru UE's, and have never been disappointed 🖤🖤🖤 See you soon!

The food is fresh and has lots of variety to choose from. The customer service sucks.  They don't greet you and they are impatient and shows all over their faces. There are lots of choices, so unless you're a regular, you can be overwhelmed by all that's available.  There are choices to accommodate people with varied dietary preferences. We've been here a hand full of times.  Generally it is pretty fast even with a little line.  That is baring folks that don't seem to understand that it works like a Chipotle and spend a lot of time looking over the options very deliberately.  I usually get a bowl with steak shawarma.  They have lots of options in particular when it comes to sauces and just general toppings. I appreciate their cane sugar based soda options as well as some unique lemonades.  A few times since they opened we went in and it was uncomfortably hot inside.   Overall a solid addition to the food options at Bowie Town Center.
Omg the flavors, the freshness, yess!

I come here fairly often, however the service gets worse with each visit. I literally stood in line, watched a guy place a mobile order outside the door, walk to the front of the line and his meal was fast tracked ahead of everyone else’s.  NO AC, don’t take children or elderly! They will definitely pass out.  Staff appears to have no ambition or drive to service customers.
Their choice of fresh, healthy options is wonderful!
It was clean and the service was good. Wanted to try this place because it was different. Apparently I dont like Mediterranean food. If you like Mediterranean food you may like this place.
Fresh food, authentic,  Mediterranean

The food is very good, customer service could be a bit better. It's not that the employees here are unpleasant but they could be a little more aware and responsive of certain things. For example, the soda machine was not working when we tried to dispense soda. My son went over and told them this but I didn't notice them telling people in line behind us that soda was unavailable. Also (just like at Chipotle), they are a bit stingy when doling out the food. The lady who waited on us gave me, for example, what seemed like a tablespoon full of crumbled feta. I realize that restaurants have, generally, guidelines for how much of a food item or ingredient is to be given to a customer but sometimes, it seems as if the employees are giving food by the gram. As I said, very good food but if you dine here, expect to say,  "May I have a bit more of (insert any food item here) please?"
The food was fresh and amazing.

Love the food, people and decor.  However, I don't think I will be back.  There seems to be no AC, no fans, no blinds.  The windows are huge and on the South side.  Today it must be 100 degrees in there.  I thought I was going to faint standing in a long line.  The servers are sweating, especially the guy that bakes the bread.  He is dripping sweat.  It's unacceptable to have the staff and customers suffer like this.  I will be getting my Mezeh from Annapolis.

Went in to try it for the first time. I asked the staff which was better, and their opinions differed drastically between their preference between the steak and the chicken.  To solve this debate, I got both steak and chicken.  The steak is super flavorful with the right amount of spice.  The chicken is super tender and cooked to perfection.  Ultimately, I believe the chicken to be the better of the two meats, and the staff to be awesome.  I will try the lamb the next time I come back, and I will come back.

Bowie location is bigger and brighter. Loads of options in proteins, toppings, sauces, and base. Delocious looking healthy drink options and the soft chocolate chip cookie was loaded with chips. Friendly staff, clean interior and exterior and sports an interesting seating couch. All in all a good visit.
I rarely give 5 stars but there are few places to get fast healthy and delicious tasting meals. This is one and you will not be disappointed. Friendly staff and a few sweet treats too!

2nd time to this location. Not as good as the Mezeh in Annapolis. Tastes a bit different. Comparatively smaller portions in general and they only give you a half of piece of pita now...

They were low on rice and close to the end of night but, willing to refresh eventhough I opted for brown rice.Thank you Jose for the end of the night pairing!!!P.S. The spicy hummus, eggplant were my favs.

Despite some reservations about going to a Mediterranean Chipotle style line serving restaurant, actually really enjoyed the food!  There are lots of choices and you can pile items on, within reason:)

Mezeh is new to town center. I gone there twice b/c I really like the food and easy atmosphere. I've only tried the chicken shawarma as my protein selection. I wish it was bit more spicier. The choice of toppings are healthy and delicious. The S'hug sauce was my choice and it has a fair amount of kick to it without being too spicy for enjoyment. Yes, I reccomend the joint and will be going back soon.

Food is very good no long lines or waits staff is informative and patient. New to the town center and stays open later than all the other food places in the town center other than the surrounding restaurants.
